# Folio Project Rules

## Firebase Database
- ALL Firestore operations must reference the "folio-nicco" database, NOT the default database
- Use `getFirestore(app, 'folio-nicco')` for all environments
- Never use `getFirestore(app)` without specifying the database ID

## File Structure
- All project files and directories must be created under the /src directory
- Use Next.js pages router format: /src/pages/
- Components go in /src/components/
- Utilities go in /src/lib/ or /src/utils/

## Tech Stack
- Next.js with TypeScript and React pages in the /pages/index.tsx format
- Firebase for all backend services (Auth, Firestore, Storage, Functions)
- Deploy to Vercel
- Use the design tokens and UI components from /src/styles/globals.css

## Authentication
- Use Firebase Auth with email/password and Google OAuth
- Store user profiles in Firestore under "folio-nicco" database
- Follow the data model from docs/Data-Model.md

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Use semantic CSS classes from globals.css
- Follow the brand guidelines from docs/design/Brand-Guidelines.md
